    <!-- Help Content -->
    <string name="help_title">Truffle Farm Guide</string>
    <string name="help_step1_title">1. Navigating the Map</string>
    <string name="help_step1_desc">Use the search bar at the top to find your city or region. The map uses Satellite view by default.</string>
    <string name="help_step2_title">2. Adding Notes &amp; Markers</string>
    <string name="help_step2_desc">Long-press any location and select \'Add Note/Marker\' to place a pin. Each note automatically saves the date it was created.</string>
    <string name="help_step3_title">3. Farm Layers (Boundaries, Soil, Plants)</string>
    <string name="help_step3_desc">You can draw different layers on your map:\n• Farm Boundary: The main perimeter (Green)\n• Soil Area: Define soil types/notes (Brown)\n• Planting Area: Map where specific trees are (Dark Green)\n\nLong-press on the map, select the layer type, and tap to draw the shape.</string>
    <string name="help_step4_title">4. Smart Organization</string>
    <string name="help_step4_desc">In the \'My Farms\' tab, soil and planting areas are automatically grouped under the farm they belong to. You can see the creation date for every area and note. Tapping an item will take you to it on the map.</string>

